{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 2004 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.berc.org.bd/ Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission] |remarks = }}
'''Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission''' or BERC,<ref>{{cite web|title=Govt to raise funds through stock mkt for mega projects in power sector|url=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/2016/09/26/47308/Govt-to-raise-funds-through-stock-mkt-for-mega-projects-in-power-sector|website=thefinancialexpress-bd.com|publisher=The Financial Express Online Version|accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref> is a regulatory agency that regulates the gas, electricity and petroleum products in Bangladesh and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="wer">{{cite book|last1=Riaz|first1=Ali|last2=Rahman|first2=Mohammad Sajjadur|title=Routledge Handbook of Contemporary Bangladesh|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781317308775|pages=251|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nC9-CwAAQBAJ&pg=PA251&dq=%22Bangladesh+Petroleum+Institute%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjbiJfE1vjPAhWCcj4KHc80CbgQ6AEIJDAB#v=onepage&q=%22Bangladesh%20Petroleum%20Institute%22&f=false|language=en}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|title=Still no policy on using Energy Security Fund|url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2016/08/26/still-no-policy-using-energy-security-fund/|website=dhakatribune.com|publisher=Dhaka Tribune|accessdate=26 October 2016|date=26 August 2016}}</ref>
==History== The agency was created in 2004 and is responsible for the setting up of gas and electricity prices in Bangladesh. Its also arbitrates disputes in the energy industry.<ref name="wer"></ref> Its approval is need for any changes in the price of electricity.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gas, power prices to soar|url=http://archive.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2016/jun/01/gas-power-prices-soar|website=archive.dhakatribune.com|publisher=Dhaka Tribune|accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref> The [[Energy Security Fund]] is under this agency.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bapex to dig 29 onshore gas wells in two years|url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2016/09/17/bapex-dig-29-onshore-gas-wells-two-years/|website=dhakatribune.com|publisher=Dhaka Tribune|accessdate=26 October 2016|date=17 September 2016}}</ref> {{clear}}
