A '''Knudsen gas''' is a gas in a state of such low density that the [[mean free path]] of molecules is greater than the diameter of receptacle that contains it.<ref>Partington J.R. (1949) vol. 1, p. 927.</ref> The molecular dynamical regime is then dominated by the collisions of the gas molecules with the walls of the receptacle rather than with each other.<ref>Lebon, G., Jou, D., Casas-Vázquez, J. (2008), p. 192.</ref>
A flow of gas through a pipe is called [[Knudsen flow]] when it can be expressed as the difference of two independent flows, which enter the pipe through its different ends.{{citation needed|date=October 2012}}
