'''Powerex Corp.''' is the wholly owned energy marketing subsidiary of [[BC Hydro]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://vancouversun.com/business/energy/ndp-sounds-alarm-on-salaries-at-hydro-subsidiary-powerex|title=NDP sounds alarm on salaries at Hydro subsidiary Powerex|last=Olivier|first=Cassidy|date=14 April 2016|work=[[Vancouver Sun]]|access-date=22 May 2018|publisher=[[Postmedia Network]]}}</ref> Powerex buys and sells wholesale electricity, natural gas and environmental energy products and services in Western North America (WECC).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.utilitydive.com/news/canadian-power-marketer-to-be-first-international-member-of-western-eim/443969/|title=Canadian power marketer to be first international member of Western EIM|last=Walton|first=Robert|date=1 June 2017|work=Utility Dive|access-date=22 May 2018|publisher=[[Industry Dive]]}}</ref> In business since 1988, Powerex Corp. is headquartered in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]]. Powerex also markets the Canadian Entitlement energy from the [[Columbia River Treaty]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.columbiavalleypioneer.com/news/columbia-river-treaty-renegotiation-set-to-begin-in-early-2018/|title=Columbia River Treaty to be renegotiated in early 2018|last=Novak|first=Chelsea|date=12 December 2017|work=The Columbia Valley Pioneer|access-date=22 May 2018}}</ref>

